g.text: EleanorRank3Convo5 begins.

g.title: j1849123234
g.text: Hello, Drifter. I’m upset.

g.title: j617877708
g.text: What’s upsetting you?

g.title: j1421953342
g.text: Hi, upset. I’m Drifter.

g.title: j3917681405
g.text: Don’t have time right now, sorry. [End.]

g.title: j3226454946
g.text: Two things.

g.title: j2907889596
g.text: THEY HAVE DAD JOKES IN THE FUTURE

g.title: Chat ends.
g.text: Chat ends.

g.title: j3941863877
g.text: I miss wine. I’ve not had real wine in so bloody long. All the wine in Höllvania got requisitioned by Scaldra command a few days into the outbreak.

g.title: j3932856221
g.text: +10 Chemistry

g.title: j1490139046
g.text: Quincy and Arthur tried making prison hooch out of fruit ration sachets, but those of us who still had some dignity left said no. Rare moment of Lettie solidarity, that was.

g.title: j3339097262
g.text: Happy now. Thank you.

g.title: j1366821584
g.text: The other thing, the much much bigger thing, is the future.

g.title: j3447494893
g.text: It’s not your fault, but… now that I’ve seen the future through your eyes I feel miserable in a way that the usual methods won’t shift.

g.title: j2585855407
g.text: What can I do to cheer you up?

g.title: j2850089600
g.text: Usual methods?

g.title: j77571255
g.text: I don't know. Maybe an exotic dance?

g.title: j1891288606
g.text: Spending the evening with Amir listening to him enthuse about whatever comic series or retro game he’s currently fixating on.

g.title: j2712318646
g.text: Describe Ballas's death to me in loving detail?

g.title: j851220077
g.text: Surrounding myself with crystals and mentally chanting until Lettie calls the exorcist on me.

g.title: j2951348626
g.text: It's kind of you to offer, but I think this melancholy will just have to be borne.

g.title: j1463221582
g.text: This is a different kind of sad. It’s weighing me down like a soggy blanket.

g.title: j3502505444
g.text: Maybe I'll paint.

g.title: j3332404475
g.text: 1999 Höllvania is rough! Scaldra, Techrot, Void knows what else. Does the future really look that much worse?

g.title: j1511493592
g.text: Oh, come on... you're tough. You can deal with this. There's so much cool stuff here.

g.title: j4081414586
g.text: +5 Chemistry

g.title: j991024954
g.text: Look, I was never really into science fiction. Arthur went through a phase, but he always preferred the gritty army stuff. Manly men being heroes, wholesome Stories for Boys, oodles of subtext, I’m sure you know the sort of thing.

g.title: j210546252
g.text: Fine. Take me by the hand and walk me through the streets of Höllvania.

g.title: j2348278968
g.text: But I did know enough about science fiction to know that in the far far future, we are supposed to have our shit together. It’s meant to be all shiny and antiseptic. Robots do all the hard work, there’s no disease, nobody needs money, it’s all silver towers, blue skies and sexy lizards.

g.title: j349786483
g.text: I know a place where we can grab some grated turnip cakes and watch the sun go down over the remains of a school.

g.title: j2679421233
g.text: We have robots. They do do a lot of the hard work.

g.title: j44247484
g.text: But what you’re talking about is just fiction, right? So why would you expect reality to live up to it?

g.title: j2144171361
g.text: Later we can sip cocktails by the light of a burning tank.

g.title: j1397885950
g.text: Well, all right. You get a point for that.

g.title: j1935163283
g.text: Ugh. I don’t… it’s complicated. Let me explain.

g.title: j3508658103
g.text: But did those robots make life any easier for ordinary people?

g.title: j843302184
g.text: I’m not saying I expected the future to look like a children’s comic book. I just mean there was this optimism associated with it.

g.title: j413038803
g.text: Or did they just become something else to take for granted?

g.title: j3767460349
g.text: I think we all just took it for granted that however shitty things might be right now, we’d sort it out eventually. Our civilization is meant to progress. We started out smashing each other over the head with clubs and after a few thousand years we’d figured out ways to sort our differences out without doing that.

g.title: j1809952806
g.text: You're determined to see the worst in everything, aren't you?

g.title: j1281484030
g.text: Fine. We didn't cure exploitation by having robots.

g.title: j3712550707
g.text: People are still people, however much technology changes.

g.title: j226219887
g.text: I'm sorry we let you down?

g.title: j1828189308
g.text: Obviously.

g.title: j3591331644
g.text: Right. That's what's so disappointing.

g.title: j3063139454
g.text: Bingo. You’ve put your finger right on what I find so depressing about all this.

g.title: j430270618
g.text: Precisely.

g.title: j2451126565
g.text: That's how you know what needs to be changed.

g.title: j517302136
g.text: You're advanced, but you were meant to be ENLIGHTENED too

g.title: j3821378736
g.text: You had all this incredible, magical technology at your fingertips and all you did with it was find new ways to exploit each other. Science made us less equal, not more.

g.title: j3929102032
g.text: Thanks for bearing with me. I know it's a lot.

g.title: j2736299933
g.text: Um, polite reminder that I didn’t do ANY of that?

g.title: j2385914267
g.text: I'll send your complaint on to the Orokin.

g.title: j374273682
g.text: +15 Chemistry

g.title: j4063234409
g.text: Oh Gods I don’t mean you personally. I mean your era.

g.title: j3869230364
g.text: If anything you went backwards. God-kings in the flesh! Of all the things to reinvent, you reinvented THEM.

g.title: j2211972787
g.text: The Tenno killed the Orokin. Did you forget that part?

g.title: j2437873804
g.text: No. I didn’t forget the part where the emotionally abused orphans murdered the immortal elite. I just love that bit. If I close my eyes I can almost imagine the screaming.

g.title: j1710606982
g.text: Fine. The future’s a mess. You can focus on that if you like.

g.title: j148346353
g.text: That... is... something I'd be careful admitting to people.

g.title: j1818514085
g.text: I’m with the people who are trying to make it better.

g.title: j3575777313
g.text: ... is irony obsolete in the future too?

g.title: j367054140
g.text: +20 Chemistry
